{{BLP sources|date=March 2015}} {{Infobox person | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1996|7|20}} | birth_place = [[Union City, California]], U.S.<ref name="Variety" /> | occupation = {{hlist|Actor|comedian}} | yearsactive = 2012–present }} '''Joey Bragg''' (born July 20, 1996)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/radiodisney/posts/10155906268270360:0|title=Radio Disney|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=15 September 2017}}</ref><!-- NOTE: Source only confirms day-of-birth, not a year or an age... --> is an American actor and comedian. He is known for his role as [[Liv and Maddie#Joey Rooney|Joey Rooney]] in the [[Disney Channel]] sitcom ''[[Liv and Maddie]]'', which aired from 2013 to 2017. He also played Peter Magoo in the 2012 television film ''[[Fred 3: Camp Fred]]'', and co-headlined the 2015 [[Disney XD]] television film ''[[Mark & Russell's Wild Ride]]''.<ref>{{cite news |author=Denise Petski |url=http://deadline.com/2015/09/joey-bragg-sean-giambrone-mark-russells-wide-ride-disney-xd-photo-1201511755/ |title=Joey Bragg & Sean Giambrone On ‘Wild Ride’ For Disney XD — First Photo |work=Deadline Hollywood |date=September 1, 2015 |access-date=2017-05-20}}</ref> Bragg has a successful stand-up comedy career.<ref name="Variety">{{cite news | author = Tara McNamara | url = https://variety.com/2012/tv/news/joey-bragg-teen-comic-on-fast-track-1118058867/ | title = Joey Bragg: Teen comic on fast track | work = Variety | date = September 13, 2012 | access-date = 2017-05-20}}</ref>
He is [[Jewish]].<ref>http://talknerdywithus.com/2016/05/15/exclusive-interview-with-liv-and-maddies-joey-bragg/</ref>
